La terminologie mobilise des repr=E9sentations de terme et des
d=E9finitions de concept qui peuvent =EAtre aussi bien verbales que non
verbales. Ainsi, la norme ISO 704, portant sur les principes et
m=E9thodes terminologiques, cite les trois types de d=E9signation que sont
les termes, les appellations et les symboles. Ces derniers =AB
constituent une aide importante pour la communication internationale =BB
en =AB v=E9hiculant directement les informations =BB. La norme ISO 10241-1,
relative aux =AB Articles terminologiques dans les normes =BB, parle,
quant =E0 elle, explicitement de =AB repr=E9sentations non verbales =BB =AB
utilis=E9es par convention =E0 la place d'une d=E9finition =BB =96 une
illustration est parfois plus explicite qu=92une d=E9finition en langue.

Les repr=E9sentations verbales et non verbales des concepts apparaissent
dans de nombreuses terminologies de disciplines scientifiques et
techniques. C=92est en particulier le cas du domaine des textiles, au
c=9Cur des activit=E9s du "Danish National Research Foundation=92s Centre
for Textile Research=94, o=F9 les repr=E9sentations verbales/et ou non
verbales - sont utilis=E9es depuis plusieurs mill=E9naires. Surtout les
repr=E9sentations de tissu se configurent en diagrammes et logogrammes
unissant d=E9signation et d=E9finition. L=92 =AB armure de toile =BB, qui se
r=E9sume en figures , codes et termes, en est un exemple.

Les soumissions portant sur les aspects, tant th=E9oriques
qu=92applicatifs, des repr=E9sentations verbales et non verbales en
terminologie, sont les bienvenues.

La Journ=E9e d=92=E9tude TOTh 2013 commencera par la pr=E9sentation de trav=
aux
men=E9s par le "Danish National Research Foundation=92s Centre for Textile
Research=94 sur les repr=E9sentations verbales et non-verbales dans le
domaine du textile et une pr=E9sentation sur le concept de =AB design =BB
comme cadre de recherche par l=92Universit=E9 de Southern Denmark - SDU.

/-----------

It is a great pleasure to announce an international workshop on the
theme of representation of terms and definitions of concepts in verbal
as well as nonverbal forms. The ISO standard 704 "Terminology work =96
principles and methods" mentions three types of designation =96 terms,
appellations and symbols. The last of these constitute an important
aid in international communication by transferring the information
directly. The ISO standard 10241-1 =93Terminological entries =96 General
requirements and examples of presentation=94 explicitly mentions the
nonverbal representations used instead of definitions. An illustration
is sometimes more explicit than a language definition.

Verbal and nonverbal representations of concepts show up in a number
of terminologies of scientific and technical disciplines. This is
especially the case for the activities at the The Danish National
Research Foundation=92s Centre for Textile Research which show that
verbal and nonverbal representations have been used for several
millennia. In the field of weaving, in particular, weaving
representations for basic and derived weaves are configured in
diagrams and logograms, thus collapsing designation and definition. A
good example of this phenomenon is the basic weave =94tabby=94 which can
be designated by figures, codes and terms.

We welcome presentations about theoretical and applied aspects of
verbal and nonverbal representations in terminology.

The TOTh workshop will begin with a presentation of the work of the
The Danish National Research Foundation=92s Centre for Textile Research
about the verbal and nonverbal configurations in the field of
textiles, and a presentation on the concept of design as a theoretical
framework by the University of Southern Denmark, SDU.

